To calculate the LIX (Läsläshetsindex, or 'Readability Index' in English) score of the Swedish text, we'll use the formula:

LIX = (A + B + C) / D

Where:
- A = Total number of words in the text
- B = Total number of sentences in the text
- C = Total number of long words in the text (long words have 6 or more letters, ignoring proper nouns and other exceptions)
- D = Total number of short words in the text (short words have fewer than 6 letters, ignoring proper nouns and other exceptions)

